On Thu, Apr 29, 1999 at 06:27:04AM -0400, Michael Slone wrote:
> I submit the following Proposal, "Patch Rule 107", delimited by '----------' at
> either end, and pay 0.3 P-Notes to increase its Priority by 0.3 .
> 
> ----------
> Amend Rule 107 by replacing the sentence reading
> 
>       Any proposed Rule Change must be written down (or otherwise
>       communicated in print media) before it is voted on. 
> 
> with one reading
> 
>       Any proposed Rule Change must be sent to the Public Forum before
>       it is voted on.
> ----------

This has a number of problems, I'm afraid:

The first is that it will not do what you want. Rule 107 has power 3, so
you'll need a proposal with Adoption Index 3 or more to amend it. AIs 
have to be set when the Proposal is made, or else they default to 1. 
(See Rule 594)

Secondly, Rule 1483 already requires that Proposals go to the Public 
Forum. Isn't that good enough?

Thirdly, there's not much point in putting such a condition in a high
power rule, when the definition of "Public Forum" is in a much lower
powered rule. If I wanted to get around your restriction, I could just 
amend Rule 478 to say that imagining something in my head is equivalent
to sending it to the PF. So your proposal actually weakens R107, by
making it rely on concepts defined in lesser rules.

If I remember rightly, you proto'd this earlier. I'm sorry I didn't
point out these bugs before it got to this stage.

