Now simplified due to Murphy (Thanks Murphy).

Protoposal,  "The Treasuror" 


Create a rule titled "The Treasuror" with the following text

There exists the office of Treasuror.

As soon as possible after the beginning of the quarter, the Registrar 
shall initiate an Election for Treasuror.  The Office of Treasuror 
shall only be elected at the time specified by this Rule, Rules to the 
contrary notwithstanding.

Each Nominee for Treasuror shall submit a valid Protobudget by the end 
of the Nomination Period, else their Nomination is automatically 
withdrawn.

A valid Protobudget must contain all information that the Treasuror's 
Budget is required to contain.

If a Nominee submits multiple Protobudgets during the Nomination 
Period, only the last one is considered.

When the Vote Collector announces the Candidates for the office of 
Treasuror to the Public forum at the end of the voting period, e shall 
also list the last valid Protobudget posted by each Candidate.

As soon as possible after the election of a Nominee to the office of 
Treasuror the Nominee's Protobudget becomes the Treasuror's budget, 
and shall be posted to a public forum again by the Treasuror.

If there are no candidates for the office of Treasuror or no one is 
elected to the office of Treasuror.  The Treasuror's budget shall 
remain the same as in the previous quarter.

The Treasuror does not receive a monthly salary but instead receives a 
payment of VTs as set in the Treasuror's budget as soon as possible 
after e is elected.


Create a rule titled "The Treasuror's Budget" with the following text.

The Treasuror's Budget shall include the following: 

(1) The salary of every officer that receives a monthly wage.
(2) The unemployment benefit.
(3) The payment of the Treasuror.
(4) Any other material that is required by the rules to be in the 
Treasuror's budget.

The above shall be given in integer multiples of 0.1, of the Basic 
Officer Salary, between 0 and 4 times the BOS inclusive. (E.g. 3.2*The 
BSO).

If there is no valid version of the Treasuror's budget, there shall be 
a budget created as soon as possible by the chancellor.  This budget 
shall contain all the information that is required to be in the 
Treasuror's budget and shall be set, as best as is possible to the 
values of the previous quarter.  The resultant budget shall be 
considered to be the Treasuror's Budget.  The Chancellor shall post 
this budget to the public forum.




Amend rule 1858 to read

Unemployment Benefits

      As soon as possible after the beginning of each month, the
      Registrar shall pay out to every Player who does not receive any
      Officer's Salary for the previous month an unemployment benefit
      as set in the last Treasuror's budget.



Amend Rule 1607 to read

The Promotor

      There shall exist the Office of the Promotor.  The Promotor
      shall receive a salary as set in the last Treasuror's budget.

      This rule will amend itself after two quarters have passed.  
      The amended rule will read as the version of this rule did 
      when it had an amendment number one less than it 
      currently does.




Amend Rule 1449 to read,

The Assessor

      There shall exist the Office of Assessor.  The Assessor
      shall receive a salary as set in the last Treasuror's budget.

      The Assessor shall also receive a Commission. At the end
      of the Voting Period for a Proposal, the Assessor shall
      pay out to emself an amount equal to 5% of the VTs spent
      on voting on that Proposal.



Amend rule 889 to read.

Clerk of the Courts

      There shall exist the Office of Clerk of the Courts.  The
      Clerk of the Courts shall receive a salary as set in the last 
      Treasuror's budget.



Amend rule 559 to read

The Registrar

      There shall exist the Office of Registrar.  The Registrar
      shall receive a salary as set in the last Treasuror's budget.


Amend Rule 1051 to read

The Office of the Rulekeepor

      There shall exist the Office of Rulekeepor.  The Rulekeepor
      shall receive a Salary as set in the last Treasuror's budget.

      The Rulekeepor shall maintain a complete list of all Rules.  The
      Short Logical Ruleset constitutes the Rulekeepor's Official
      Report. In addition, the Rulekeepor shall post the Full Logical
      Ruleset to the Public Forum at least once each month.


Amend Rule 1785 to read

The Accountor

      There is an Office of Accountor, whose Salary is as set in the 
      last Treasuror's budget, and whose responsibility it is to be 
the 
      Recordkeepor for Voting Tokens. The Accountor's Report 
      includes the number of Voting Tokens possessed by each entity 
      which possesses them, and any changes thereto since the last 
      posting of the Accountor's Report.



Amend rule Rule 1647 by replacing the text

      "The Speaker-Elect receives no salary for filling the Office of
      Speaker-Elect."

With,

"The Speaker-Elect receives a salary as set in the last Treasuror's 
budget, for filling the Office of Speaker-Elect."



Amend Rule 1377 by replacing the text,

      "The Herald shall receive a salary equal to 2 times
      the Basic Officer Salary."

With,

"The Herald shall receive a salary as set in the last Treasuror's 
budget."



Amend Rule 1878 by re placing the text,

      "There is an Office of Scorekeepor, whose Salary is 1.5 times 
the
      Basic Officer Salary,"

With,

"There is an Office of Scorekeepor, whose Salary is as set in the last 
Treasuror's budget."




